The paper proposes a new method for causal structure learning using a graph autoencoder framework and gradient-based optimization. This approach falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves training a model to learn from data. Additionally, the use of nonlinear structural equation models suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of causal structure learning also involves combinatorial optimization, which could place it under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the scalability and efficiency of the proposed method, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
